<subSubSection id="34646E42B5AF53A7A2C2E99144C517D4" pageId="0" pageNumber="155" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="F7798D00335FFB21869AA7F192586DA6" pageId="0" pageNumber="155">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D569E3BC10FFE0D4BAE52DEA40D36029" pageId="0" pageNumber="155">
<taxonomicName id="30E814B923A6272BD7F6ACEC6F0F24BE" baseAuthorityName="A. H Clark" baseAuthorityYear="1949" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiacanthidae" genus="Ophioplinthaca" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ophioplinthaca semele" order="Amphilepidida" pageId="0" pageNumber="155" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="semele">
<emphasis id="907A9BB33952443C31628E689F23F79A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="155">Ophioplinthaca semele</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was first described by A. H 
<bibRefCitation id="2C762FE23886F6E187979597D98A493F" author="Clark, AH" journalOrPublisher="Bishop Museum" pageId="0" pageNumber="155" pagination="3 - 133" refId="B11" refString="Clark, AH, 1949. Ophiuroidea of the Hawaiian Islands. Bulletin of the Bernice P. Bishop Museum 195: 3 - 133" title="Ophiuroidea of the Hawaiian Islands. Bulletin of the Bernice P." volume="195" year="1949">Clark (1949)</bibRefCitation>
in the genus 
<taxonomicName id="338AD00C2BC54EDB0E4058163ED4783D" authorityName="Lyman" authorityYear="1869" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiacanthidae" genus="Ophiomitra" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ophiomitra" order="Amphilepidida" pageId="0" pageNumber="155" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="270E41488DFF00A55DFB855ADA3B076E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="155">Ophiomitra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, then redescribed by 
<bibRefCitation id="F942742D70995AB82DB99CF543F0957F" DOI="https://doi.org/10.7717/peerj.11566" author="Chen, W" journalOrPublisher="Ecology and Evolution" pageId="0" pageNumber="155" refId="B2" refString="Chen, W, Na, J, Zhang, D, 2021a. Description of three species of ophioplinthacids, including a new species, from a deep seamount in the Northwest Pacific Ocean. PeerJ. https://doi.org/10.7717/peerj.11566" title="Description of three species of ophioplinthacids, including a new species, from a deep seamount in the Northwest Pacific Ocean. PeerJ." url="https://doi.org/10.7717/peerj.11566" year="2021 a">Chen et al. (2021a)</bibRefCitation>
, and that recent study included rich morphological information. 
<taxonomicName id="FEECC756181ECF1CD5216E96A5EBF0C2" baseAuthorityName="A. H Clark" baseAuthorityYear="1949" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiacanthidae" genus="Ophioplinthaca" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ophioplinthaca semele" order="Amphilepidida" pageId="0" pageNumber="155" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="semele">
<emphasis id="BB88127E3A566C4826A2DD0C88A6B8E8" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="155">Ophioplinthaca semele</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the present study concurs largely with the holotype description and 
<bibRefCitation id="DF97B898E0074D6FD6B3270620E89036" DOI="https://doi.org/10.7717/peerj.11566" author="Chen, W" journalOrPublisher="Ecology and Evolution" pageId="0" pageNumber="155" refId="B2" refString="Chen, W, Na, J, Zhang, D, 2021a. Description of three species of ophioplinthacids, including a new species, from a deep seamount in the Northwest Pacific Ocean. PeerJ. https://doi.org/10.7717/peerj.11566" title="Description of three species of ophioplinthacids, including a new species, from a deep seamount in the Northwest Pacific Ocean. PeerJ." url="https://doi.org/10.7717/peerj.11566" year="2021 a">Chen et al. (2021a)</bibRefCitation>
, but it differs slightly in the disc stumps at the periphery of the disc. According to the holotype description, the disc stumps had a thorny tip or three thorns in the disc center, but at the periphery these stumps were smooth. Our specimen has a crown of somewhat longer thorns, both in the center and periphery of the disc (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="5A71EBC863728779E9D44BAA8C13BFB9" captionStart="Figure 14" captionStartId="F14" captionText="Figure 14. Ophioplinthaca semele (A. H Clark, 1949) (IDSSE-EEB-SW 0113: A-H) A dorsal disc B ventral disc C center of the disc D radial shield E oral frame F ventral arm G dorsal arm H lateral arm; Ophioplinthaca defensor Koehler, 1930 (IDSSE-EEB-SW 0112: I-Q) I dorsal disc J ventral disc K center of the disc L disc spine M oral frame N lateral disc O dorsal arm P ventral arm Q lateral arm. Abbreviations: as adoral shield, dap dorsal arm plate, das dorsal arm spine, gs genital slit, j jaw, lap lateral arm plate, m madreporite, os oral shield, rs radial shield, ts tentacle scale, vap ventral arm plate, vas ventral arm spine. Scale bars: 2 mm (I); 1 mm (A, B, F-H, J, N-P); 500 µm (C-E, K, M, Q); 200 µm (L)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1099.76479.figure14" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/682275" pageId="0" pageNumber="155">14A-H</figureCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="8CA42A2B42AB27AAD8BDB64488D772CE" baseAuthorityName="Lyman" baseAuthorityYear="1878" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiacanthidae" genus="Ophioplinthaca" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ophioplinthaca dipsacos" order="Amphilepidida" pageId="0" pageNumber="155" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="dipsacos">
<emphasis id="F165B56783F705C3775DEFF231DF5B72" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="155">Ophioplinthaca dipsacos</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Lyman, 1878) is one of the species that most closely resemble 
<taxonomicName id="9058EC2D5D101465F6E5D944A58F67F8" baseAuthorityName="A. H Clark" baseAuthorityYear="1949" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiacanthidae" genus="Ophioplinthaca" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ophioplinthaca semele" order="Amphilepidida" pageId="0" pageNumber="155" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="semele">
<emphasis id="B379FFD89ED9A6164A40D6AD370C8B7A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="155">Ophioplinthaca semele</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having a similar number and shape of arm spines, radial shield characters, number of lateral oral papillae, similar disc spines, and separated dorsal and ventral arm plates, but it differs in the number of tentacle scales at the first to third tentacle pore, and in the shape of the tentacle scale (Table 
<tableCitation id="508FE4795BA140DB8342E19FEC89C6F0" captionStart="Table 3" captionStartId="T3" captionText="Table 3. Tabular key to all species of the genus Ophioplinthaca. Abbreviations: ASE arm segment, ASS Adoral shield spine, DAP dorsal arm plate, DAS dorsal arm spines, L length, LOP lateral oral papillae, VAP ventral arm plate, VAS ventral arm spines, VMT ventralmost tooth, W width." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/9F85B69899787A840F669B2BD815C383" pageId="0" pageNumber="155" tableUuid="9F85B69899787A840F669B2BD815C383">3</tableCitation>
). Moreover, 
<taxonomicName id="17E539CB944214CF10D81833ADBAE499" genus="O." lsidName="O. dipsacos" pageId="0" pageNumber="155" rank="species" species="dipsacos">
<emphasis id="2BAFB1F381D54E36395D7DD71EA7DAD3" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="155">O. dipsacos</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was recorded from the Gulf of Mexico, far from the known distribution of 
<taxonomicName id="3A3F8AEF1698EFB68A2DE85989B9757F" genus="O." lsidName="O. semele" pageId="0" pageNumber="155" rank="species" species="semele">
<emphasis id="89B8DFF458453DE71570B2AC5A074546" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="155">O. semele</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Lyman, 1878). 
